For plotting, using tools from package uedge_mvu.


##-Check out from github: 
git clone https://github.com/umansky/uedge_mvu

##-Install: Set up uedge_mvu as a package by running the following command inside the directory containing
setup.py:
pip install --editable . --user

This way, you can do from uedge_mvu import * from anywhere, and python
will read the files in e.g. ~/Desktop/uedge_mvu. Note that this will
break and you will need to reinstall if you change the path of
e.g. ~/Desktop/uedge_mvu.
